title: german text for NOTRE DAME de paris Victor Hugo
description:
VICTOR HUGO NOTRE DAME DE PARIS (1827)     GERMAN TEXT IN TWO VOLUMES





    Personally i always thought that the cathedral was a symbol for the old 

    culture being devorated by the coming of the age of democracy , 

    but rumours about a desire of Victor Hugo to prevent the future centuries

    of the problems posed by monsters-eating-radiactivity has made this book

    a real need all across the corridors of power in Brussels.
